decision makers, and privileged communication. Many of these obscure the element of interdependency. The authors argue that interdependency is a fruitful critical - and human - framework by which to re-evaluate some of our traditional legal concepts. The book will be of interest to law and society scholars and students, as it presents a different critical framework through which to analyze traditional human relationships.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAttorney and clientzCanada. 0aInterpersonal relationszCanada. 0aPersons (Law)zCanada. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aCampbell, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlanagan, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKerr, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLauzière, Lucie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosiers, Nathalie Des, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSossin, Lorne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485025440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774850254423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774850254/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles